<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>First, let me say that I presume this is a problem with the documentation rather than the code.</p>

<p>In section 6.1 in the manual, we're told that "without any arguments, constructing an instance returns an object in the default locale with the current date."  Example 6.2 shows us just that:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?php
   require_once 'Zend/Date.php';
   $date = new Zend_Date();
   // Output of the current timestamp
   print $date;
?&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>This doesn't work.  The first argument is actually required (currently).  Again, I presume it's a documentation issue, but I'm not sure.</p>

<p>And, for those that may not be sure, the static method, Zend_Date::now(), will probably suffice for most situations.  :-)</p>

<p>Thanks.</p>

