        <div class="body">
            <p>The default behaviour of date objects is always that if no value is given, the actual timestamp should be used.</p>

<p>See date('Ymd'); for example or the new date object from php.</p>

<p>So we also have to do standard behaviour.
Which means that our constructor has also to allow loosing this parameter.</p>

<p>The following examples work:
new Zend_Date();
new Zend_Date('ja');
Zend_Date::now();</p>

<p>Fixed with SVN 3131 but only for I18N branch.</p>

